<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Question on Necromancers in pvp</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ice">Ice</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:30 p.m. 2/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Question on Necromancers in pvp<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Ok i have a question on Necromancers. I have a dark elf Necromancer, just hit level 13, and i was fighting someone the other night and i casted heat blood on them, well they gated off and died. And they used the /tell command and told me they were reporting me for using a Dot spell, and that they lost a level because of the spell. Ok from what i see if this is true and im not allowed to cast these spells, then what use is a necromancer? These spells are the most damaging spells i have at my disposal. I mean pets more or less suck now, that every, "Tom, Dick and Harry", casts invisible on my pet, and *Blamm*, its gone. So now im left with no pet, cloth armor, a worn staff, and not being allowed to cast my best spells. So my question's are A. Is casting invisible on my pet a bug, and do they plan on fixing it? B. Are these Dot spells goin to be fixed or, am i just not allowed to use them? I see no reason to play a necromancer if A and B arent fixed, because i am more or less playing a very weak spellcaster if thats the case.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
